My pleasure. I am glad you enjoyed it. Although I've got to say that the ending was probably one of my favorite parts. The end is supremely disturbing and although I don't really agree with his description of what we are I think it does put a lot of things (ideas/beliefs) into perspective. Perhaps he went a bit too far though.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Science is founded on being able to prove things, and they can prove their idea's all the way back to the creation of life, but for the life of them they can't explain how that first organism came into being. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
