There's beer in hell? Woohoo!! Seriously though (or facetiously, whichever works) I figured it's a rant forum and I had to rant at someone. *wink*<br>
<br>
On the topic of prayer in schools: prayer is an individual activity which can just as easily occur in the silence and privacy of one's own mind as anywhere else. There is no way to ban prayer in school. If a child wishes to pray, she may do so at any moment no matter what else is going on.<br>
<br>
What was banned, and I'm completely in favor of the ban, was the practice of organized prayer in schools. Children of different faith, and children of no particular faith, were made to feel different unless they conformed and bowed their little heads and folded their little hands and pretended to be what they were in fact not...Christians. <br>
<br>
